sql:
SELECT name
FROM customers
WHERE customer_id IN (
  SELECT customer_id
  FROM credit_applications
  WHERE application_id NOT IN (
    SELECT application_id
    FROM loan_assignments
  )
);

SELECT loan_type, AVG(repayment_period) AS AverageRepaymentPeriod
FROM loans
GROUP BY loan_type;

external_knowledge:
- "captain of the ship" metaphorically refers to the loan officer; 
- "navigating the stormiest waters" implies dealing with a large number of loan applications;
- "bearing the most sails" metaphorically means handling the most loan applications.

